oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Songwriter Session - Adam Wright - 2015-03-21
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance by singer songwriter Adam Wright from the Ford Theater at the Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum on March 21, 2015. Presented in support of the exhibit Alan Jackson: 25 Years of Keepin’ It Country
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Adam Wight;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Includes questions from the audience. Performances include; The Way I'm Living -- No Truck, No Boat, No Girl -- Unidentified Song (That Girl?) -- Unidentified Song (Happiness Depends?) -- So You Don't Have To Love Me Anymore - Wrong About You -- The One You're Waiting On -- We'll All Drink Money -- Unidentified Song (Born To Dream?).
